Synopsis:
   set status_channel [<text>]

Description:
   This variable sets the format of the current channel name in the status
   bar of the current window.  If the client is not on a channel in the
   current window, nothing is displayed.

   This string is represented by %C in the STATUS_FORMAT string.  The %C
   will expand to the current channel name in the STATUS_CHANNEL string
   before being placed in STATUS_FORMAT.

Examples:
   Customizing the channel name display in the status bar:
      /set status_channel Chan: %C

See Also:
   join(1); set(4) status_format; window(4) channel

